review_blob: Festival Hoogeveen (20151220): from tap. A cloudy dark yellow beer with a good white foam layer. A normal aroma of slightly malt and somewhat sweet/fruity. a sweet taste with fruit (orange, somewhat banana) and not so much bitter in the aftertaste. Nice beer, but not really exiting.

Festival Hoogeveen (20151220): from 33 cl bottle. A clear golden yellow beer with a white thin foam layer. The smell is slightly sweet, but more esters/fruity (apple, orange). Taste is somewhat sweet, but very fast a good hop bitter character appears, which become dry in the aftertaste. Good balance. Nice beer.
beer_name: Saint Germain Page 24 Rserve Hildegarde Blond

review_blob: Beer with a dense white foam layer and a clear golden yellow colour. Aroma is light malty (biscuit-like), lot of fruit/esters (orange, banana), somewhat floral character. Taste is somewhat sweet with fruit (orange, peach, pear, banana) with a somewhat dry bitter aftertaste. Coriander?

HOME (2016.01.02): 35.5 cl bottle. A clear dark yellow beer with a good off-white head. Aroma is light malty. For the rest a nice hop smell with fruitiness (apple, pear, light citrus-like). Taste is light sweet whit somewhat malty, which give enough body for the dry hop-bitter character of this beer. Citrus-like fruity/marmalade. In the finish somewhat yeast and biscuit. Reasonable beer, but not a topper.

HOME (20160101): 33 cl bottle. BB 12.16. Gushing, when opening bottle. So a yeasty beer in the glass (dark yellow) and an off-white cola-like foam. Aroma of malt, somewhat citrus-like hops and slightly fruity (apple & peach). Not niche is the yeast. Taste is malty, somewhat bitter (hops) and slightly sour. And yeast. Not a fresh beer.

HOME (01.01.2016): 33 cl bottle; BB 04.17. According the label is this beer brewed at Sint Servatimus in Schijndel. A beer with a good white foam layer and a dark yellow colour. Can be pour clear in the glass. Aroma is light malty and fatty (Higher alcohols, soap). Taste is somewhat malty and has a thick feeling (fatty). Somewhat sweetness, but hardly no hop bitter. Not a great beer.

HOME (20160101): 30 cl bottle. BB 17.07.17. A yellow, cloudy beer with a good, thin white foam layer. Aroma is somewhat malty (Biscuit), Fruity (pear, esters/red fruit) an slightly hoppy (not so fresh). Small sweetness in taste with malty (grain-like) in the begin. Aftertaste is slightly hoppy with citrus-like end. Somewhat biscuit. The taste could be more fresh.

Hoogeveen (20151220): 33 cl bottle on a festival. Dark brown beer with a brownish small head. A smell of roasted malt, caramel, chocolate with a very nice smoked flavour. A sweet taste of chocolate, black cherries and a nice smoked taste. Fruity: raisins, apple and liqueur. A sticky end and somewhat dry bitternesb. Complexe aroma and taste. Very okay. Good balance.

HOME (20160101): 30 cl bottle, tht 30.01.16. A clear dark brown beer, with a good brownish head. Smell is somewhat roasted barley, yeast ans slightly hop. Not nice is the buttery smell. A sweet somewhat roasted barley and spicy. Part of the sweet is replaced by bitter of malt and hops. Full body, but not really in balance. Missing the fresh taste of hops and malts.

Hoogeveen (20151220): 33 cl bottle at festival. A dark brown beer with a brown thin foam. Smell of roasted malt, chocolate, black cherries, raisins, liqueurs. A sweet taste of chocolate, raisins and black cherries. Sweetness stays, but a malty bitter comes up. Full bodies. Alcoholic taste. Beer which is good in balance.

HOME (20160101): 33 cl bottle with a label of India Pale Ale; bottle conditioned and 5.3% ABV. A beer with a good off-white foam layer and a clear red-copper like colour. Very nice aroma of light malty/caramel and a good smell of hopbitter. Taste is somewhat sweet (caramel), but fast a dry hopped taste is coming up. Body is medium, but okay.

HOME (20151227); 33 cl bottle. A clear beer with a goldyleew/orange color. An off-white very good head. Aroma is somewhat malty (biscuit), light alcoholic, fruity (light citrus, marmalade, peach, raisins). Taste has some sweetness, fruity (see aroma), light spicy (cardamon), malty (biscuit) . Body is medium/full with sweetness (caramel-like) and in the end also hop bitterness. Somewhat sticky and dry-bitter.

HOME (20151227) 33 cl bottle. A amber colored, clear beer with an off-white thick foam layer. The aroma has some malts/sweet (caramel),. Somewhat sour (Brett) and nice fruity (apple, raisins) ans what wine. Taste is malty/caramel, fruity (apple, light grapefruit) somewhat yeast. A nice sour taste which is compensated by light sweet and some hop bitterness.

HOME (20151226): 33 cl brown bottle; BB 19.10.2015. On the label the beer is named: Hite Ice Point. A clear yellow beer with a good white-colored head. The smell is somewhat malty (wheat-like) and slightly hoppy. Taste is slightly sweet with a reasonable body and hardly no hopbitter. Drinkable but not so nice.

HOME (20151226): 33 cl brown bottle; BB 30nov15. A clear yellow beer with a thin white foam layer. The aroma is slightly malty and somewhat oxidation. Tast is sweetness with hardly no hop bitterness. Body is very thin, because of the use of rice and corn.

Home (20151225): 35.5 ml brown bottle. A clear, yellow beer with a thin white foam layer. Smell is slightly fruity and malty. With a little smell of corn or wet paper. In the taste somewhat sweetness en hardly no hop-bitter. The body is thin.

Home (20151225): clear 35.5 cl bottle. Clear yellow beer with a thin white head. Smell is some sweetness/fruitiness with a somewhat malty, biscuit-like finish. Taste is neutral whit a light malty character. Missing the hop bitter in the taste. So not special.

Home (20151225): Green 33 cl bottle. BB Mar 16. ABV 4.78% !!! Nice thin layer of white foam. Clear yellow beer. In the aroma somewhat hop bitter and a slightly fruity (esters). Neutral taste with somewhat fruitiness (apple, peach). The body is thin. Aftertaste is slightly sweet and somewhat bitter dryness. The version from the can have slightly more body with a light malty taste. Good drinkable beer
Home (20151225) The aroma is not so fresh with a smell of malt. Also some hopbitter. The taste is slightly sweet with a nice hopbitter aftertaste. The body is a little thin.

HOME 20131215 (33 cl bottle): Gushing. So hardly no foam in the glass. The cloudy beer is amber with floating paricles. Not a nice view. The aroma is mainly sweet, caramel, amlty with some citrus-like hop, some fruit (raisins), little spicy (ginger), but an off-flavour of bread/biscuits and some yeast. The taste is also maily sweet, caramal and malt. In the sweet aftertaste (sticky) you will find some bitterness and later also some sour tones. In the taste also some yeast and bread. Unfortunally not a nice palet.

HOME 20131215 (33 cl bottle): A yellow colured beer with in the beginning thick white foam layer, bit disappears fast to hardly nothing. The beer is cloudy whit medium yeast particles. Not a nice view. Aroma of malt, yeast, some fruit (orange, appel, peache). Some higher alcohols and slightly parfum. The taste is sweet/malty with fruitiness (orange, peach) and some hops (light citrus-like) in the aftertaste. The mouthfeel is somewhat viscous, fatty-like. Strange beer with some nice flavors combinations, but not so fresh.

HOME 20131215 (33 cl bottle): A yellow coloured beer with some cloudiness and a white foam layer (good in begin, decreasing fast). The aroma is some malty (wheat-like), fruit (orange, green apple, pear, some grapefruit), spicy (somewhat coriander) and some hops. Taste is some wheat, fruit (orange and apple, some lemon), somewhat coriander. In the aftertaste somewhat sourness (mainly from the carbonization) and some bitterness. A medium body. Looks like a Belgium white beer, but a little too sour, but refreshing.

HOME 20131215 (50 cl bottle): A nice white head, like a thin foam. The cloudy beer has a light yellow colour. Taste is wheat, somewhat citrus/lemon, banana and cloves. Also some yeast, sweetness and spicy. The slightly sweet taste will be combined with lot of wheat ans cloves. Also some banana. The somewhat lemon in combination with a lot of CO2 gives the beer een somewhat sourness in the aftertaste. The fruitiness and more the spicy taste with the sweetnes stays in the aftertaste, where we also found some bitterness. A good example of a weissbeer.

HOME 20131103 (33 cl bottle for the USA): A clear yellow beer with a smooth thin white foam. The smell and taste is a little fatty. Aroma of some malts and hops. Also some hoppiness in the finish. Drinkable beer, but not so really fresh taste. Maybe better drinkeble when it is really fresh (beer best before end 18/02/2014). The taste of the beer from tap was better at the brewery.

HOME 20130804 (30 cl bottle): A nice white head. Can be poured nearly clear in the glass, but with more cloudiness the beer is better. The colour is yellow. In the aroma some malt/wheat, really banana and some other fruits (orange) in the minor. The taste is a little sweet with in the finish some sourness and hops. In the aroma and tast also some cloves tones. For a German Weizen the beer is somewhat low in carbonation. A moderate body. For the rest is the beer good in balance, but not really comparable with a German Weizen.

HOME 20130804 (30 CL bottle): A clear yellow beer with a thin white head. Not too much aroma of malt, flowers and hops. With the body of a pilsner we taste a light sweetness and a good soft hop bitter in the finish. The beer is a little bitter dry. A good pilsner,

HOME 20130802 (30 cl bottle): A clear amber beer with a good foamy head. The crme coloured foam stick to the glass. The aroma is of ambermalt (slightly roasted), caramel, some hops and some vanilla. A somewhat malty taste with sweetness/caramel. In the finish still some sweetness with an upcoming bitter from the hops and somewhat from the malts. The mouth feel is somewhat sticky sweet and bitterdry. Also in the taste some vanilla and fruitiness (apple, peach, cherry-tones)

HOME 20130802 (4.5 % ABV, 237 ml can): A clear, light yellow beer with a good, white foam layer, but the most disappears fast. The small amount of aroma is malty and some floral hops. Also a slightly off-flavour. The taste is hardly nothing, even a little watery. We can recognize some sweet and too less hops for a nice pilsner.

HOME 20130731 (33 cl can, export version): A clear, straw-yellow beer with a thim white foam layer. No much aroma and taste. We recognize some malt, light floral and some straw in the aroma. The taste is somewhat sweet, light floral and hop notes in the finish. The bitter is a little metallic hard.

HOME 20130731 (33 cl can): A clear dark yellow beer with a good white foam layer, which became very less after some minutes. The aroma is slightly malty with herbs/hoppy tones and some biscuits. It taste in the beginning as a pilsner, but in the finish we have some sourness and hop bitter. Also some floral flavour. After a while the mouth feeling is somewhat sticky.

HOME 20130731 (50 cl bottle): A clear, golden yellow coloured beer with a good nice white head. The aroma is somewhat sweet/caramel (and malt tones) and a little hops. Not nice is the slightly buttery flavor. The taste is malty with caramel sweetness (at the end even somewhat sticky). An upcoming hoppy bitterness. Finish is caramel/sweet and hops. The taste is also somewhat soapy/higher alcohols and probably a medium-full body (sweetness/buttery). I taste the beer before and then it was better.

HOME 20130730 (33 cl bottle, 8.5 % ABV): A clear, dark amber (slightly red) coloured beer with a thin, fine beige head. Aroma: roasted malt, sweet, caramel (licorice). Coffee, toffee and raisins. The taste is some roasted malt and sweetness. Further fruity (raisins), caramel, and chocolate. In the final sweet, a malty, roasted bitterness and alcohol. A full body beer as can be expected for a dubbel. The beer is somewhat sticky in the mouth.

HOME 20130730 (33 cl Bottle): A light yellow beer with a bubbly white head. A slightly malty aroma with a good hop flavor. Also some fruitiness of orange and a little spicy of pepper. The taste is slightly sweet, but the hop bitterness is fast upcoming whit a bitter dryness in the aftertaste. A good alternative for a pilsner.

HOME 20130730 (33 cl Bottle): A yellow clear beer with a good foamy head. A somewhat malty aroma with sweetness and fruity/esters (apple, orange, peach). Some hops flavour and slightly yeast. The taste is slightly malty and some sweetness. The hop bitter comes a little later in the taste. For the rest a fruity taste of apple and orange. The body is medium-full, but a little too sweet. In the final it is light alcoholic and we recognize some yeast.

HOME 20130713 (33 cl bottle): A clear, gold-yellow beer with a white, thin head. A nice flavor of slightly malt/sweet/sour with fruitiness of apple, pear and some citrus-tones. Also some vanilla. In the mouth a slightly malty taste (give the beer some body), sweetness and a nice refreshing sour-tones. Hereby fruitiness off apple, pear, peach, some grapefruit and floral notes with vanilla. The alcohol of the triple you can feel. The aftertaste is light sweet and some sourness. A beer with a good balance. With some yeast from the bottle we can taste some more bitterness.

HOME 20130415 (33 cl bottle): A clear orange-yellow beer with a thick, white foam layer. The aroma is direct in the direction of American hops: citrus-like, grapefruit, orange, lychee, vanilla, but also some sweetness (caramel) and light malty. The taste starts with some sweet/caramel (light malty), which stay also in the aftertaste. A nice hop bitterness is coming up very soon (grapefruit, peach and orange). Also some floral taste, herbs (green hops, grass) and spices. The sweetness (maybe a little to much, somewhat sticky) give the beer body and a balance against the dry hop bitterness. So a nice mouthfeel with the fruitiness of the beer. A good American style IPA.

HOME 20130415 (33 cl bottle); A nearly clear, yellow beer (more yeast in the bottle) with a good white head. The aroma is some wheat, a little too much coriander, somewhat marmalade and flowers/honey. The taste starts a little sweet with a feeling of wheat. Somewhat herbs and spices (coriander), little sour in the middle of the taste and same bitterness (hop) extra in the aftertaste. Also curacao peels. The balance of the taste is okay. With the yeast the body increase and the taste become better. Than also some bananas in the taste. Later the beer becomes a little sticky.

HOME 20130415 (33 cl bottle): A good crme-coloured head and an amber clear beer (some yeast in the bottle). Aroma: Slightly roasted malt, sweet/caramel, some chocolate and raisins/dried fruit. The taste is more or less like the aroma. The beer is somewhat sweet in the beginning and some upcoming bitter in the short aftertaste. This bitter comes from the roasted malt. The beer becomes after a while a little sticky. We can also taste some yeast.

HOME 20130401 (33 cl bottle, duvel type; so another type bottle and other label than pictured): Starts with gushing and a lot of beige-coloured foam. An amber coloured, clear beer. Aroma: sweet & caramel, malt, slight chocolate, some coriander, bread, yeast, slightly sourness/oxidation (looks like older beer), raisins. The taste is sweet (caramel, brown candy sugar) with an upcoming malty bitterness. Fruity (apple, dark fruit, berries). Some coriander and some other spices. Also some oxidation in the taste which give the fruity taste of port. The aftertaste is still sweet (sticky) and some malt bitterness. Overall is this a reasonable beer with a lot of aroma and taste, but is already a little to old.

HMOE 20130331 (33 cl longbottle): The beer pours with a big brown head, a amber colour and tiny particels. The aroma is malty (slight roasted), caramel, raisens, vanille. Also some off-flavour of yeast, buttery and soap. The taste starts sweet with caramel, but also a not-nice small sour taste. In the end some malty bitterness. Furtheer esters, vanille and yeast. The finish is somewhat dry from the sour and bitterness. After a while even some sticky feeling.

HOME 20130329 (33 cl bottle): A clear amber coloured beer with a thin off-white-coloured foam layer. In the aroma we found some malt (light roasted), caramel sweet,  liquorice. Also some off-flavours of fatty, soap, higher alcohol-like things. The taste is sweet, malty, some caramel. The bitterness and nice roasted malt we can not found in this winterale. The palate is somewhat thick of soap/higeher alcohols. Not a clear and nice beer.
UPDATED: MAR 29, 2013

HOME 20130303 (33cl bottle, long version) A yellow beer with some cloudiness and a big white head which stick to the glass. The aroma is somewhat malt, grass-like, citrus-like hops, some spicy. A light yeast smell. A very small sweetness (and malt) is nearly immediately taken over by fruity bitterness of citrus and marmalade. In the aftertaste is the beer very hop-bitter dry. A little too much, because the other nice taste is in the background. Also some yeast and spicy is coming up.

HOME 20130303 (33 cl bottle, long version) An amber coloured clear beer with a big stable beige head which sticks to the glass. A smell of sweetness and caramel, some roasted malt, Fruity (raisins) and slightly chocolate. The taste is somewhat sour (not nice), caramel, little roasted malt and bitterness from hops and malt. In the aftertaste we found bitterness from hops and malt, but it is also not that nice. Somewhat phenolic-like bitterness

Home 20130217 (30 cl bottle): A clear amber coulored ("copper-like") beer with an off-white head, which became very thing. In the aroma we found caramel, roasted barley, chocolate and nuts. The what sweet beer as the the taste of roasted malt, chocolate, some nuts and grape. The aftertaste is bitter from hops and roasted (chcolate-lake) malt. the end is somewhat sticky and dry-btterness.

Home 20130217 (30 cl bottle): A cloudy, yellow beer with a thick white head, which stay long on the beer. We smell wheat and fruityness from banannes, yellow pears, appel and peach. The strong carbonated beer has a slightly seetness, but in the aftertastte some sourness and bitteerness. For the rest we observe wheat, fruit (citrus-like, banana, yellow pears and peach.

Home 20130217 (30 cl bottle) A clear golden-yellow beer with an good white head. The aroma is malty, which give a sweetnes impression. Also slight cloves. The tate is malty with some sweetnes. In the aftertaste the light sweetnes stay and a light dry-hoppy taste came up. It is a somewhat malty tated pilsener.

Home 20130217 (25 cl bottle): A light yellow beer with a thick white foam layer. The beer is poured clear, but has some sediment inn the bottle. In the aroma we find: floral, grass, clove, light malt, some roasted bread. The taste is some what sour with a hopbitteer aftertaste. The body is a little thin. A lot of carbonation. For the rest in the taste: hop. malty, floral, grass. This is a beer with an low alcohol, enough taste but not in balance.

HOME 20130217 (25 cl bottle): A clear yellow beer with a nice white foam. Some aroma of malt (wheat-like) en some hops. The same in the taste with a slightly bitterness in the aftertaste. It is a standard pilsener. Good, but not extreem.

HOME 20130127 (33 cl bottle): A clear dark rubbish beer with a big brownies creamy head. The aroma is roasted malt, dark chocolate,  slight coffee, raisins and slightly hint of citrus-like hop. The taste is sweet with fast a heavy bitter taste of hops and roasted malt. Further dark chocolate, coffee, fruity (rasins, pruims), some ctitrus-like hop and vanille. A full body beer with heavy, complete and complex aroma and taste. Somewhat sticky and bitter-dry in the aftertaste. Also some alcohol.
